    <div class="instructions">
        <h2>How to Play: "Sensory Profile" (The Card Sort)</h2>
        <p><strong>Goal:</strong> To discover and create a visual map of your personal sensory needs. Remember, each player needs their own set of cards to sort!</p>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>Get Your Cards:</strong> Print and cut out all the cards from the three decks (❤️ Likes, ⚡ Triggers, and 🌿 Soothers/Helpers). Mix them all into one big pile.</li>
            <li><strong>Set Up Your Sorting Area:</strong> On a large, flat surface, make labels for your sorting categories. Good ones to start with are: <strong>Like</strong>, <strong>Dislike / Trigger</strong>, <strong>Soother / Helper</strong>, <strong>Neutral</strong>, and <strong>Unsure / Want to Explore</strong>.</li>
            <li><strong>Sort the Cards (One by One):</strong> Draw a card from your big pile. Read it and think about how that specific thing makes <em>you</em> feel. Place the card under the category label that fits best for you. There are no wrong answers!</li>
            <li><strong>Review Your Profile:</strong> Once all the cards are sorted, take a look at your piles. This is your personal sensory profile! Notice any patterns. This is the foundation for your sensory safety plan and for playing the "Sensory Solutions" game next.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <h1>Printable Sensory Profile Cards</h1>

